17. Addendum: Sharethrough Consumer Privacy Notice Addendum for California Residents
1. Introduction
Sharethrough, Inc., its affiliates, and subsidiaries (“
Sharethrough
” or
“
we
” or “
us
” “
our
”) respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your information.
This User Privacy Notice (“
Privacy
Notice
”) outlines our practices for collecting, using, maintaining, protecting, and disclosing (“
Processing
” or “
Process
”) your Personal Data. Sharethrough may Process your Personal Data when you visit third-party websites, mobile applications and over-the-top (“
OTT
”) devices (such as SmartTVs or applications on your Smart TV)
(“
Partner Sites
”),
that use our advertising platform (the “
Advertising Platform
”) to serve targeted advertisements to you based on your personal interests (“
Advertisements
”).
As you navigate through and interact with Advertisements served by our Advertising Platform on Partner Sites, we may use automatic data collection technologies to collect certain information about your equipment
and
also
details of your interaction with Advertisements. This information includes “personal information” or “personal data” as defined under applicable law, including the laws of Canada, Quebec, Europe, the United Kingdom, the United States, including California and Virginia and more. “
Personal Data
” as referred to in this Privacy Notice is any information, whether combined or on its own, that directly or indirectly identifies or could reasonably identify you.
Please read this Privacy Notice carefully to understand our policies and practices regarding your Personal Data and how we treat it. We recommend that you read this Privacy Notice  in full; however, the links at the top of the page are intended to help you navigate to sections that are relevant to the information in which you may be interested.
This Privacy Notice applies to information we collect when you interact with Advertisements on Partner Sites. It does not apply to:
Information collected by Buyers, other providers, or any third parties with whom we conduct business;
Information related to your employment or potential employment with us. This can be found on our
Candidate Privacy Notice
;
Information collected by our website. This can be found on our
Website Privacy Notice
; or
Information we collect in our business relationship with you. This can be found on our
Corporate Privacy Notice
.
We recommend that you also consult the privacy policies of the third-party digital properties you use to become familiar with their privacy and data collection uses and practices.
2.
About Us
Sharethrough is a supply-side platform (“
SSP
”) and advertising exchange. Our technology enables us to conduct online auctions for advertising space on
Partner Sites
. These third-party partners are collectively referred to as “
Partners
” in this Privacy Notice.
Through the Advertising Platform, Sharethrough connects Partner Sites to buyers of advertising space that wish to bid on Partner ad space inventory. Buyers include advertisers and intermediary demand-side partners (
collectively
, “
Buyers
”). Buyers work with Sharethrough based on contractual relationships to deliver ads based on your personal interests and to reach their target audiences.
3. The Information We Collect
Information Sharethrough and our Partners collect
Sharethrough and our
partners (Partners, Buyers, and any other type of business involved in the ad tech ecosystem) operate on an open-source protocol to provide our services, known as Open RTB. This open-source protocol allows the collection of information such as:
Cookie identifiers – A cookie is a small file placed on the browser of your computer.
Sharethrough cookies
Our Advertising Platform uses persistent cookies (which stay on your computer until you delete them) to provide our services. These cookies are used to display promotions or advertisements on Partner Sites based on your interests. They collect information about your activities on our Partner Sites and other sites to provide you with Advertisements that match your interests.
We may collect and store cookie identifiers
from a variety of domains, and store such identifiers at either our domain or our partners’ domains. We also engage in cookie syncing, which is the matching of our cookie identifiers with those of our clients and other partners.
Third party cookies
In addition to Sharethrough cookies, Buyers may also drop persistent cookies on your browser. Buyers include companies such as Google to deliver the best advertising opportunities to its clients. Traffic Clients and other data subjects can consult Google’s policies to learn more about Google’s processing policies. In particular, Google may use remarketing tags (please visit https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites to learn more about the third parties Google works with) and other advertising cookies.
Web Beacons – These are small electronic files on Partner Sites
(also referred to as clear gifs, pixel tags, and single-pixel gifs) that permit our Advertising Platform, to perform activities, such as counting users who interacted with certain Advertisements and understanding the scope of that interaction.
Clickstream data – This includes the Advertisements you have clicked or that have otherwise been viewable to you, the amount of Advertisements displayed and the amount of time the Advertisement was viewable to you
.
Device information – As applicable, general information such as device type (e.g., laptop, mobile, TV), model, manufacturer, operating system, time zone, telephone carrier information, network information (e.g., WIFI), and mobile application information. Mobile device information includes standard mobile advertising identifiers located on every mobile device. These are:
IDFA
– advertising identifier used on Apple’s iOS devices; and
Google Advertising ID
(
AAID
or
GAID
) – advertising identifier used on Android devices, to track your use of mobile apps on your device(s).
Geolocation data – Location information such as city, country, zip code/postal code, and/or longitude/latitude.
Date and time of your visit to a Partner Site
IP address
User agent – A short bit of text that attempts to describe the software/browser (the “
Agent
“) that is making the request to a website. The user agent often includes descriptions of the operating system and device type that the Agent is running on.
Information about your internet connection and, and other communication data and the resources that may be a result of your access to Advertisements on Partner Sites.
The above is a comprehensive but non-exhaustive list of the personal data we may collect and or receive about you. The full list can be found on the
Open RTB protocol spec
, as amended from time to time.
4. Why We Collect Your Personal Data
Sharethrough may Process your Personal Data to:
Engage in real time transactions for the sale of Advertisements
and deliver such ads to you on our Partner Sites;
Show you Advertisements on the Partner Sites that are more relevant to your interests
(for example, Advertisements based on other websites and online platforms that you have visited)
;
View and enforce user opt-out choices; to access your opt-out choices for us and other third-party advertisers,
click here
;
Detect and stop click fraud on the Partner Sites;
Audit your interactions with Advertisements, including, but not limited to: counting advertising impressions to unique visitors, verifying positioning and quality of ad impressions, and auditing compliance with any applicable specification and other standards;
Help maintain the safety, security, and integrity of Sharethrough’s Advertising Platform, detect security incidents, protect against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent, or illegal activity related to the use of the Advertising Platform;
Identify and repair errors that impair existing intended functionality in the Advertising Platform;
Carry out our obligations and enforce our rights arising from any contracts entered into between the operators of our Partner Sites and Buyers
;
Conduct internal testing, research, analysis, reporting, and product development, including to develop and improve our Advertising Platform; and
Process your Personal Data for any other purpose with your consent.
Kindly note, Sharethrough does not measure your browser history, or engage in retargeting, reidentification, or audience segmentation; however, some of our partners may engage in these practices. They may also Process your Personal Data
.
In addition, Sharethrough does not participate in cross-device linking. Cross device linking is the process of tracking a user across multiple devices, for example, across a SmartTV, mobile, and/or website; some of our partners may engage in cross device linking.
5. Lawful Basis for Processing Your Personal Data
Sharethrough will always Process your Personal Data if it has a legal reason to do so. Below are the lawful bases under which we may Process your Personal Data.
Consent.
As we do not have a direct relationship with you, we require
Partner Sites to obtain any consents from you with respect to our Processing
of your Personal Data, as required by applicable law, and particularly under European data privacy law. Please contact the websites and mobile and Smart TV applications you visit regarding any methods that they provide to obtain consent. If you do not consent to our Processing of Personal Data as set forth in this Privacy Notice, please review the choices that the operators of the Partner Sites may provide you or do not use the applicable Partner Sites;
Legitimate Interests.
In limited circumstances, we may Process your Personal Data as necessary for our legitimate interests in accordance with this Privacy Notice. We do not
Process your Personal Data if your interests or rights and freedoms outweigh our legitimate interests. Our legitimate interests may include measuring ad performance
‍
.
As Required by Law.
We may also Process your Personal Data when we are required or permitted to by law; to comply with government inspections, audits, and other valid requests from government or other public authorities; to respond to legal requests such as subpoenas; or as necessary for us to protect our interests or otherwise pursue our legal rights and remedies (for instance, when necessary to prevent or detect fraud, attacks against our network, or other criminal and tortious activities), defend litigation, and manage complaints or claims. We use every effort to protect your privacy in such circumstances.
6. Special Categories of Information
Sharethrough does not ask you to provide, and we do not knowingly collect, any “special categories” of Personal Data, or sensitive data, including Personal Data that reveals your racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, or trade unions membership, or Personal Data concerning your health or data concerning your sex life or sexual orientation or history of criminal convictions.
We also do not collect information that directly identifies you, such as your identification or financial information.
7. Children Under the Age of 13
Our Advertising Platform may collect information from a child (as defined by applicable law) because of a child’s interaction with some Partner Sites. We do not control these Partner Sites, and the operators of
those Partner Sites are solely responsible for obtaining any required parental consents and for all other compliance requirements related to the collection and use of information from children. If you believe we might have any information directly from a child without required consents, please contact us.
8. Disclosure of Your Information
We may disclose Personal Data that we collect, or that you provide, as described in this Privacy Notice as follows:
To Buyers for real time transactions for the sale of Advertisements using the Open Real Time Bidding protocol;
With other Buyers, through the synchronization of our cookie identifiers with the identifiers of other third parties; these partners are intermediaries that source advertisements related to your personal interest.
With our identity partners (independent companies that qualify you into broad interest-based categories in order to serve you Advertisements based on your personal interests
such as LiveRamp or Unified ID 2.0);
Fraud prevention vendors – third-party vendors that help maintain the integrity of our services, for example, by preventing malicious software (e.g., viruses, trojans) or traffic from non-humans (i.e., robots) from loading on the websites you browse;
For any other purpose disclosed by the operators of the Partner Sites when you navigate on their website;
To our subsidiaries and affiliates;
To contractors, service providers, and other third parties we use to support our business
and who are bound by contractual obligations to keep Personal Data confidential and use it only for the purposes for which we disclose it to them. These entities provide IT and infrastructure support services along with payment processing and collection services;
To a potential or actual buyer or other successor in the event of a planned or actual merger, divestiture, restructuring, reorganization, dissolution, or other sale or transfer of some or all of Sharethrough’s assets, whether as a going concern or as part of bankruptcy, liquidation, or similar proceeding, in which Personal Data held by Sharethrough about the users of our Advertising Platform is among the assets transferred;
To comply with any lawful requests, court order, legal process, or response to any government or public authority request; including to meet national security or law enforcement requirements.
To enforce or apply our agreements with Buyers and publishers, including for billing, collection, and revenue sharing purposes; and
If we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property, or safety of Sharethrough, our customers, or others. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organizations for the purposes of fraud protection and credit risk reduction.
We do not control the collection and use of your information by third parties. Third parties we work with are under contractual obligations to use this data only for providing the services to us, and to maintain
the confidentiality of such information, as applicable. Additionally, each third party Processes your Personal Data in accordance with their own privacy policies. For more information about third parties that may collect your data, please visit
https://youradchoices.ca/choices
.
9. Automated Decision Making
Sharethrough does not use your Personal Data with any automated decision-making process, including profiling, which may produce a legal effect concerning you or similarly significantly affect you.
10. Industry Self-Regulation &  Ad Choices
Sharethrough believes in industry self-regulation
and supports multiple self-industry efforts to protect your personal data, including:
Digital Advertising Alliance (DAA)
: Sharethrough adheres to the DAA Self-Regulatory Principles for Online Behavioral Advertising. Under these principles, you have the choice to opt-out of third-party behavioural advertising preventing further collection from your browser and/or mobile device. For more information, please visit
https://youradchoices.com/control.
*
Digital Advertising Alliance of Canada (DAAC)
:
Sharethrough adheres to the DAAC’s Self-Regulatory Principles for Online Behavioral Advertising.
The Interactive Advertising Bureau (IAB):
Sharethrough strictly enforces the
IAB’s Consent Framework for managing GDPR consent for data collection and processing in the European Economic Area. This means we do not Process any Personal Data unless we receive a consent string, meaning a code that signals consent status
shows that you consented to receive personalized advertising
or allow us to process your Personal Data on the basis of legitimate interest. Sharethrough’s identification number within the framework is 80. Sharethrough also strictly enforces the IAB CCPA Compliance Framework for technology companies to manage data collection and processing in California.
Trustworthy Accountability Group (TAG)
:
Sharethrough is a member in good standing of
TAG.
*Please note, while this section is intended to demonstrate the self-regulatory initiatives that Sharethrough adheres to, we added information relating to the DAA’s opt-out per request from the BBB National Programs; an independent, non-profit organization that provides third-party accountability and dispute resolution services for the DAA.
