18. Sharethrough Consumer Privacy Notice Addendum for California Residents
This notice to California residents (“
California Notice
”) is provided under California law, including the California Consumer Privacy Act (“
CCPA
”), Cal. Civ. Code 1798.100, et seq. This notice supplements our Privacy Notice by explaining your privacy rights if you are a California resident, providing our “notice at collection,” and providing certain mandated disclosures about our treatment of California residents’ information, both online and offline.
We recommend you review the Privacy Notice in full, along with the California Notice to have a complete overview of Sharethrough’s privacy practices.
Sharethrough Platform
Our Advertising Platform collects information that could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, with a particular consumer, household, or device (“
Personal information
”).
Categories of Personal Information Collected
Please find below the categories of Personal Information Sharethrough collects, and has collected, over the prior twelve (12) months through our Advertising Platform:
Category
Examples
Identifiers
Online identifiers, Internet Protocol address, device information (e.g., mobile or laptop, MAC or WIN), user agent, web beacons, clickstream data (i.e., that you clicked on an ad), model, manufacturer, operating system, time zone, telephone carrier information, network information (e.g., WIFI), mobile application information and any additional information provided to us through the OpenRTB protocol.
Internet or other similar network activity
Information on a consumer’s interaction with a website, application, or advertisement.
Geolocation data
Location information such as city, country, zip code/postal code, and/or longitude/latitude.
Purpose(s) of Collecting your Personal Information
We may share, or have shared, your Personal Information for behavioural advertising purposes over the prior twelve (12) months. This may be referred to as the “sale” of your Personal Information for monetary or other valuable consideration. Sharethrough does not actually “sell” your Personal Information as is commonly understood to require an exchange for money; we simply share it with our clients to provide our services.
Sources of Personal Information
Sharethrough obtains the categories of Personal Information listed above indirectly from you by participating in a real time auction for the delivery of personalized advertising to you on our Partner Sites. We may also obtain the above categories of Personal Information from our synchronization of cookies with the providers of other digital advertising exchanges.
Disclosure of your Personal Information to Third Parties
Sharethrough may disclose your Personal Information to a third party for the delivery of personalized advertisements to you on our Partner’s websites and applications as described elsewhere in our Privacy Notice. When we disclose Personal Information for a business purpose, we enter a contract that describes the purpose and requires the recipient to not use it for any purpose except performing the contract.
In the preceding twelve (12) months, Sharethrough disclosed the following categories of Personal Information for a business purpose to the listed categories of third parties:
Category
Examples
Categories of Third Parties
Identifiers
Online identifiers, Internet Protocol address, device information (e.g. mobile or laptop, MAC or WIN), user agent, web beacons, clickstream data (i.e. that you clicked on an ad), model, manufacturer, operating system, time zone, telephone carrier information, network information (e.g., WIFI), and mobile application information.
Demand side partners, advertisers, identity partners, fraud prevention partners, cloud-based service providers.
Internet or other similar network activity
Browsing history, search history, information on a consumer’s interaction with a website, application, or advertisement.
Demand side partners, advertisers, identity partners, fraud prevention partners, cloud-based service providers.
Geolocation data
Location information such as city, country, zip code/postal code, and/or longitude/latitude.
Demand side partners, advertisers, identity partners, fraud prevention partners, cloud-based service providers.
Your Rights and Choices
The CCPA provides consumers (California residents) with specific rights regarding their Personal Information. This section describes your CCPA rights and explains how to exercise those rights. You may exercise these rights yourself or through your authorized agent. When these rights overlap with the rights described in our User Privacy Notice, we will generally endeavor to provide you with the broader rights, unless doing so would be a violation of law.
Access to Specific Information and Data Portability Rights
You have the right to request certain information about our collection and use of your Personal Information over the past 12 months (a “
Right to Know
” request).
You can make a Right to Know Request by visiting the
Sharethrough’s User Rights Page.
Once we receive your request, we will disclose to you:
The categories of Personal Information we collected about you.
The categories of sources for the Personal Information we collected about you.
Our business or commercial purpose for collecting or selling that Personal Information.
The categories of third parties with whom we share that Personal Information.
We will provide you with a copy of your Personal Information in a portable and, to the extent technically feasible, readily reusable format that allows you to transmit the Personal Information to another third-party.
Deletion Request Rights
You have the right to request that Sharethrough delete any of your Personal Information that we collected from you and retained, subject to certain exceptions.
To exercise the right to
delete your
Personal Information
by visiting
Sharethrough’s User Rights Page.
Personal Information Correction Rights
You have the right to correct any
Personal Information
we have about you. Please keep in mind that due to the technical nature of the data we collect, it may be impossible/impractical for us to correct or change your
Personal Information
.
If you feel the personal information we have about you is incorrect and would like us to rectify it, please
contact us and we will do our best to facilitate your request
.
Restrictions / Right to be Forgotten / Opt-Out of Processing.
You have the right to restrict our Processing of your
Personal Information
under certain circumstances. For example, you can request for Sharethrough to restrict the use of your
Personal Information
.
You can restrict processing by setting your browser to refuse all or some browser cookies, or to alert you when cookies are being sent to facilitate the restriction of processing. If you restrict such processing, please note, you will still see Advertisements on Partner Sites, they just may not be relevant to your interests. You can find more information about cookies at
http://www.allaboutcookies.org
and
http://youronlinechoices.eu
.  Please
contact us if you require additional information
.
Opt-outing out of browser, mobile, CTV
.
